  tabs: it is under docs/guides tabs and titled "Build your first app" in the left-menu

  ignore "Create a Hello World app".
  ignore "Start the Android Basics course". 

  choose "Browse learning resources", https://developer.android.com/courses
    ignore "New! Android Basics with Compose"
    other interesting courses: "pathway Modern Android app architecture", 
                               "pathway Kotlin coroutines", 
                               "pathway Kotlin for Java developers"

    choose "Android Basics in Kotlin", 
      https://developer.android.com/courses/android-basics-kotlin/course

      6 units: "Unit 1: Kotlin basics", "Unit 2: Layouts", "3 Navigation", 
                 "4 Connect to the internet", "5 Data persistence", "6 WorkManager"

      Unit 2: "pathway 1 get user input in an app part 1", "pathway 2 ... part 2", 
                "3 display a scrollable list"
                all dated September 2020.
        https://developer.android.com/courses/android-basics-kotlin/unit-2

      Unit 3: 4 pathways dated December 2020, and one May 2020.
        https://developer.android.com/courses/android-basics-kotlin/unit-3

        Concepts: intent, extra, activity lifecycle, fragment, architecture



